A community meeting in Rosettenville in southern Johannesburg to discuss crime has degenerated into violence. JOHANNESBURG - A community meeting in Rosettenville in southern Johannesburg to discuss crime has degenerated into violence.Locals have blocked roads with burning tyres, they're calling for alleged drug lords and brothel owners to leave the area.Police have fired rubber bullets and used stun grenades to try and disperse protesting residents.The police's Kay Makhubele says, The situation in Rosettenville is tense, community members are out on the streets saying they want these drug dealers to be removed from the area. They re also calling for the prostitutes to be kicked out of the area. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)